## Proposed Architecture

The system will use a strict Service-Oriented Backend Architecture, augmented with Orchestration and Scheduling layers.

### Backend Structure (`/backend`)
```
backend/
└── app/
    ├── api/            # API routing only
    ├── core/           # Config, security, DB session, Celery setup
    ├── models/         # SQLAlchemy ORM models (supporting Soft Deletes)
    ├── schemas/        # Pydantic validation schemas
    ├── repositories/   # DB access layer
    ├── services/       # Core business logic
    ├── orchestration/  # Business Orchestration Engine (Workflow central coordination)
    ├── rules/          # Business Rules Engine
    ├── scheduler/      # Background Scheduler & Automation Services
    ├── analytics/      # Analytics & Business Health Monitoring
    ├── master_data/    # Master Data Management (MDM)
    ├── inventory/      # Reservation & Location Management
    ├── manufacturing/  # Multi-Level BOMs & Production
    ├── purchasing/     # Procurement Decision Engine
    ├── delivery/       # Delivery Management Module
    ├── approvals/      # Approval Workflow Framework
    ├── notifications/  # Event-driven WebSocket pub/sub
    ├── audit/          # Audit Compliance & Activity Timeline
    ├── ai/             # Future-Ready AI Integration Layer (modular for LLMs)
    └── utils/          # Helpers
```

### Database Schema Additions (PostgreSQL)
All transactional and master data tables will implement **Soft Delete** (`is_deleted`, `deleted_at`).
New/Updated core structures:
1. **Master Data**: `products`, `customers`, `vendors`, `product_categories`, `uom` (Units of Measure).
2. **Warehouse & Locations**: `warehouses`, `locations` (Raw Material Stores, Production Areas, Finished Goods, Dispatch). Inventory will be tracked per location.
3. **Multi-Level BOMs**: `bom`, `bom_components` (supporting hierarchical parent-child relationships).
4. **Delivery Management**: `delivery_orders`, `delivery_order_lines`.
5. **Approvals**: `approval_requests`, `approval_history`.
6. **Core Additions**: `stock_reservations`, `activity_logs`, `roles`, `permissions`, `role_permissions`.

## Core Engines & Enterprise Systems

### 1. Business Orchestration Engine
Acts as the central coordination layer for all ERP workflows. Every business event passes through here to ensure dependencies are managed (e.g., SO -> Inventory -> MO -> PO -> Delivery -> Notifications -> Audit).

### 2. Multi-Level BOM & Manufacturing
Supports hierarchical BOMs (sub-assemblies). MOs will recursively calculate component requirements across all BOM levels.

### 3. Warehouse & Location Management
Inventory is location-aware. Stock movements, reservations, and receipts occur between specific locations (e.g., Receiving -> Raw Materials -> Production -> Finished Goods -> Dispatch).

### 4. Delivery Management
Automatically generates a Delivery Order from a fulfilled SO, managing dispatch details, inventory assignment from the Dispatch Area, and shipment tracking.

### 5. Approval Workflow Framework & Business Rules Engine
- **Approvals**: Configurable chains for high-value POs, MOs, and pricing.
- **Rules Engine**: Centralized evaluation of conditions (low stock, delays, triggers) to decoupled automated actions.

### 6. Background Scheduler
Executes periodic operations: low-stock monitoring, analytics refresh, delayed order detection, and housekeeping.

### 7. AI Integration & Business Health
- **AI Layer**: Modular design ready to plug into LLMs (OpenAI, Gemini) for intelligent procurement, conversation, and insights.
- **Business Health**: A top-level score calculated from Sales, Inventory, Manufacturing, and Procurement KPIs.

